Questions that arise after the accident: Are stewards on the bus illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long distance is forbidden
In the context of the tragic accident on the bus of the Student Agency near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can travel within the coach during the journey.
"If one wanted to strictly and formally respect the law, the activity of a steward is contrary to the law on road traffic," said the spokesman of the Ministry of Transport Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in question, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck that crossed the road to the coach.
The girl was, unfortunately, sitting next to the driver, on the most dangerous seat of the vehicle, although she had two other seats at her disposal.
However, the coach may have an accident or even a sudden brake, also when the steward serves the coffee or distributes the newspapers.
What matters is whether the coach is equipped with standing or not.
If this standing equipment is not approved, passengers shall remain seated.
The Student Agency long-distance buses do not have standing seats; this was confirmed in Aktuálně.cz by the director of Radim Jančura.
"This is an issue that we dealt with with the department and, at first, it prohibits any movement of passengers.
Then they canceled it and we got the passengers to go to the toilet during the journey provided they had their own seats," he revealed his position.
The law ignores the steward
"There is no unambiguous legal interpretation of the steward role - there is no legal requirement to deal with that role.
On the other hand, there is no legal requirement to prohibit the carrier from offering services.
The law on road transport only knows the term "receiver of a vehicle"; it does not define its rights and duties," adds the spokesman Hanzelka more ambiguously.
Josef Pokorný, the head of the road traffic department, believes, on the contrary, that the law sufficiently addresses the problem.
"It depends on the fact that the coach has permission in its approval to offer standing places.
Everything is in there," he says.
The coaches are divided into urban areas, where there are standing places and a limited maximum speed, intercity with standing places and a higher permissible speed and long distance coaches without standing places with the highest maximum permissible speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
Like on the plane, says an expert
Jaroslav Ho+n, expert at BESIP (road traffic safety) in transport safety, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"In regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of service in aircraft.
There, too, it is not sure when turbulence will occur and the air hostess can hit her head."
"Now, in the event that the coach would have stopped abruptly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
In the same way as in an urban bus or tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of stewards with internal requirements," he says and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the problem is not solved.
Jančura is ready to abolish these services
Student Agency is the only bus carrier to offer steward services.
He hires two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their job to be a risky job.
"Nevertheless, as soon as I feel that this is a risky job, I will delete it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper upon boarding.
It would also reduce costs," he says.
The safety concern is the reason given to the absence of stewards in his vehicles by the director of the Asiana Alexey Litvine, who ensures, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
"We don't have hostesses. We've been opposed to them from the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end in a fatal accident," he said a year ago in Týden.cz.
A huge tragedy has happened
A young hostess from the Plze+ region, who had been working for the company for two years, died during the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency stop strip without using a blinker and blocked the way to the coach.
The driver of the latter tried to avoid him by means of a sudden maneuver, but he approached him by his right side.
Jančura refuses that the two seats reserved for the rest of the stewards have been sold.
"In the case of long distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these places, they are blocked."
The company intends to file a complaint against the truck driver.
For the compensation of the girl's family, the agency will not wait for the judgment of the court, but as far as the financial compensation is concerned, it also relies on the guilty party.
An amendment to the law?
Not in sight
An amendment to the Act, which has been being prepared for more than a year by a group of thirty experts from the Ministry of Transport, could provide clarification on the travel of stewards on board the coach.
"However, it did not reach any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not too interested in buses, but rather in the point system, the maximum speed on the highway and the use of the mobile while driving," says expert Ho
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider the activity of stewards as something that would fundamentally endanger the safety of passengers," concludes spokesman Hanzelka, stating that the control of the safety of coaches is under the authority of the police and the Office for Safety at Work.
