The bank's shareholders and creditors can only hope for this.
However, given the dynamics and imponderability of the crisis, there is no certainty.
It is not unthinkable that funding should not be used in its entirety.
But neither can the opposite be ruled out.
After the fact that the bank is, according to the latest press releases, still at the door of insolvency Sunday at the end of the evening, this rescue at least temporary will not succeed to reassure the minds either.
The share price fell from 75 per cent to 3.30 euros.
Bond prices, on the other hand, are particularly good.
