The most affected are the investment funds of the former daughter company Württemberg Hypo and those of course that have a life beyond 2009.
The bonds of the bank Hypo Real Estate previously seemed to be an alternative speculation investment, now their value must be considered dependent on the stability of the international banking system after the net tightening of the banking crisis and the crisis of the very institute that brought the crisis into the establishment by the takeover of the bank Depfa.
As long as the issuing institutions, governments and less affected commercial banks are still ready to support the system, it can be assumed that arrears will be eliminated over time.
Or it will happen what no one dares to hope at this moment - that the financial crisis can be overcome in the next 15 months.
But in the face of renewed noises of partial nationalization, the probability that approached safety has now become a simple, well-founded hope.
This should set aside sleepless nights primarily for long-term creditors on whether to separate themselves from their commitments.
Short-term investors can always use what they drew a line from to represent a carry-over of losses for the next few years to the next tax on capital income from automatically collected stock gains.
